                "## 1. The Recurrent Paradigm: LSTMs and Hidden State Compression\n",
                "The LSTM was the foundational architecture for Sharpe-optimised deep momentum. However, its sequential nature imposes a significant 'memory bottleneck.'\n",
                "\n",
                "### The Memory Bottleneck:\n",
                "In an LSTM, the entire history of the sequence must be compressed into a fixed-size hidden state $h_t$ and cell state $c_t$. As the lookback window increases (e.g., to 252 days), the model's ability to preserve precise information from the beginning of the window decays.\n",
                "\n",
                "### Vanishing Gradients over Long Horizons:\n",
                "Backpropagation Through Time (BPTT) requires the gradient to flow through $T$ recurrent steps. Despite the use of gates, the gradient still undergoes multiple matrix multiplications, leading to potential decay or instability over very long macro horizons."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## 2. The Attention Paradigm: Breaking the Path Length\n",
                "The Transformer architecture replaces recurrent connections with a self-attention mechanism, which directly relates every time step in the window.\n",
                "\n",
                "### Path Length Analysis:\n",
                "| Property | LSTM (Recurrent) | Transformer (Attention) |\n",
                "| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
                "| Maximum Path Length | $O(T)$ | $O(1)$ |\n",
                "| Parallelization | No (Sequential) | Yes (Global) |\n",
                "| Memory | Bottlenecked (Cell State) | Direct (Query-Key lookup) |\n",
                "\n",
                "### The Gating Gap:\n",
                "Wood et al. (2022) refer to the 'Gating Gap'—the inability of recurrent models to effectively gate and prioritize information from the distant past. The Transformer resolves this by calculating a specific attention weight $\\alpha_{t,\\tau}$ for every pair of time steps $(t, \\tau)$, allowing the model to 'jump' directly to a relevant historical regime."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
